.TH timezone 8
.SH NAME
\*Ltimezone\*O \- Sets timezone information.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\*L/usr/sbin/timezone\*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "timezone command"
The timezone command is an interactive program for setting and changing the
timezone of the system.  The program prompts you for specific information
regarding the timezone for your area.  This command must be run if the SVID-2
habitat is to be used.  Once it is run, it need not be run again, unless the
system is re-installed.
.SH RESTRICTIONS
.PP
You must have superuser privileges to use the \*Ltimezone\*O command.
.PP
Refer to the
\*ESystem V Compatibility User's Guide\*O
for information on the System V habitat.
